02/06/2003
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Deputy Finance Minister Gati Al-Jebouri submitted his resignation Saturday (31 May), citing personal reasons.
Finance Minister Milen Velchev suggested the move may be due to financial considerations;
Al-Jebouri reportedly has received offers from the private sector.
He took office about 15 months ago.
In other news, Bulgarian police have arrested three people suspected of participating in a currency counterfeiting and document forgery ring.
The arrests followed a series of raids conducted Friday.
Officials say they found equipment for printing euro and dollar banknotes, as well as stamps used by interior ministry, border control services and other state institutions.
(Dnevnik, Trud, 24 Chassa - 02/06/03;
BTA, BNT - 31/05/03)
